headline: Merck’s KEYTRUDA Wins New Ovarian Cancer Use As Valuation Gap Persists
summary: Merck (NYSE:MRK) received FDA approval for KEYTRUDA and its new subcutaneous formulation, KEYTRUDA QLEX, in combination therapies for platinum-resistant ovarian cancer. The approvals include a companion diagnostic to help identify patients who are eligible for these PD-1 inhibitor based treatments.
